item.title: Deob q's
item.dc:creator: @semaphore semaphore
item.description:
@semaphore wrote:

As ppl said, it is only the key to being banned.

You have to perform the action that puts it into the door and turns it. ie. running the deobfuscated client against the real server.

It is completely possible to use a ‘deob’ and avoid the most common forms of detection. The amount of effort needed to accomplish it is far more than the effort needed to inject.

item.title: Deob q's
item.dc:creator: @Enum Enum
item.description:
@Enum wrote:

zyle1992:

ok so i just got the deob, and i was wondering what i do with it. yah it’s a nooby question, but i heard that if you use the commands you made in you private server, then what ever the command does it will work in real runescape. is that true? also can you help me with it, thanks.

No it’s not. The commands you use are server side meaning the modifications done to the client wont make a difference in the running of those particular commands.

The deob is basicly the decompiled and deobfusicated source. The client conencts to the server, so the client is what you see and the code needed to connect in short.
